                                           String suffix)
        Create a URL by parsing the given class type and suffix. The new URL created will be: {scheme}://{api-base-url}/{account-id}/{class}/{suffix}.json Example: /api/v1.0/accounts/123/messages/count.json
        Parameters:
        clazz - class type
        suffix - string value with a suffix for the URL
        Returns:
        a new URL with with the class and suffix values

      • request

        protected static <T> T request(VivialConnectResource.RequestMethod method,
                               String url,
                               String body,
                               Map<String,String> queryParams,
                               Class<T> responseClass)
                        throws BadRequestException,
                               ServerErrorException,
                               UnauthorizedAccessException,
                               ForbiddenAccessException,
                               ApiRequestException
        Taking a HTTP method, an URL, a body and query params, do a request to the Vivial Connect API and process the response returned.

        If the request does not have a body and/or query params, pass null to these parameters.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Response class type
        Parameters:
        method - a valid HTTP method
        url - request URL
        body - body or payload of the request. This is not required.
        queryParams - query params for the request. This is not required.
        responseClass - class type for map the response
        Returns:
        a response type defined
        Throws:
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs
